@c -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@anchor{random_student_t}
@deffn  {Function} random_student_t (@var{n})
@deffnx {Function} random_student_t (@var{n}, @var{m})

Returns a Student random variate @math{t(n)}, with @math{n>0}.  Calling 
@code{random_student_t} with a second argument @var{m}, a random sample of size 
@var{m} will be simulated.

The implemented algorithm is based on the fact that if @var{Z} is a normal 
random variable @math{N(0,1)} and @math{S^2} is a chi square random variable 
with @var{n} degrees of freedom, @math{Chi^2(n)}, then
@ifnottex
@example
                           Z
                 X = -------------
                     /   2  \ 1/2
                     |  S   |
                     | ---  |
                     \  n   /
@end example
@end ifnottex
@tex
$$X={{Z}\over{\sqrt{{S^2}\over{n}}}}$$
@end tex
is a Student random variable with @var{n} degrees of freedom, @math{t(n)}.

To make use of this function, write first @code{load(distrib)}.
@end deffn

